title: Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression row[0]
description: When setting a filter like 'row[0] equals to 0' or just returning a null result set.
OB: The system returns an incorrect data set result when an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set or when a null result set is returned.
EB: The system should return the correct data set result when a valid filter expression is set and should handle invalid filter expressions or null result sets gracefully.
SR: To reproduce, set an invalid filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0' and observe the result. Alternatively, return a null result set and observe the outcome.
